<LP>
   MINE SAFETY APPLIANCES Co. (Pittsburgh) -- Lee N. Short
Jr., 63-year-old chief executive officer, was named to the
additional post of chairman of this maker of plant safety
equipment, succeeding John T. Ryan Jr., 78, who retired but
remains a director. As president, Mr. Short was succeeded by
John T. Ryan III, 46, formerly executive vice president.
